title: Rice export prices worldwide 2011 - 2018 , by variety
summary: This is a multi-line chart with 5 lines representing U.S. Long Grain 2.4, U.S. California Medium Grain 1.4, Thai Parboiled 100, India 25, and Pak Basmati. The y axis denotes Price in USD per ton and the x axis denotes Year.
Overall Thai Parboiled 100 is gradually decreasing, U.S. Long Grain 2.4, U.S. California Medium Grain 1.4, India 25, and Pak Basmati are roughly constant,  throughout the Year
Throughout the period, Pak Basmati generally had the highest Price in USD per ton relative to others with an average of 1086.38, and it reached its maximum at 2013 with a value of 1372.0.
After Pak Basmati, U.S. California Medium Grain 1.4 overall has the second highest values , with a mean value of 788.4, peaking at 2014.
The botommost line, India 25,  has a mean of 373.0, and peaked at 2011.
